Vercel API requests are authenticated using an Access Token provided in the Authorization header as a Bearer token [1][2]. When making direct REST API calls, include the token in your header as shown below [1]:

```http
Authorization: Bearer <your_access_token>
```

If you are using the Vercel SDK, pass the token during client initialization [2]:

```typescript
import { Vercel } from "@vercel/sdk";

const vercel = new Vercel({
  bearerToken: "<YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE>",
});
```

Other authentication methods, such as OpenID Connect (OIDC) tokens, are used for specific contexts like Vercel Connect, internal integrations, or automated service-to-service communication [3][4][5].
